The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for localization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Received Signal Strength (RSS) fingerprint-based localization, which is a common technique used in wireless networks and falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses privacy-preserving methods for crowdsourcing, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of federated learning, which is a technique used in distributed systems and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data transmission and communication, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
